title: Ethan-Parkston Boys, MVP Girls Win SESD Cross Country Titles
text:
Ethan-Parkston Boys, MVP Girls Win SESD Cross Country Titles 0 comments 
TYNDALL – Eight was enough for the Mount Vernon-Plankinton girls and Ethan-Parkston boys, as each team posted that total in winning titles at the Southeast South Dakota Conference cross country meet on Monday at Bon Homme Country Club. 
The MVP girls put four runners in the top seven to beat out Winner 8-21 for top honors. Chamberlain’s Ella Byers won the 5,000-meter event in 18:59, easily beating MVP’s Lainey (20:32) and Lorna (20:33) Gregerson. Ethan-Parkston’s Lexi Leischner (20:46) was fourth. 
In the boys’ division, Jonah Murtha won in 17:36, leading Ethan-Parkston to an 8-27 victory over Gregory. Gregory’s Aaron Voigt (18:02) was second, followed by E-P’s Tanner Hohn (18:36) and Tucker Murtha (18:39). 
GIRLS’ DIVISION 
TEAM SCORES: Mount Vernon-Plankinton 8, Winner 21, Ethan-Parkston 27, Wagner 36, Bon Homme 52, Platte-Geddes 57
